<font color="#FF0000">ACTION IS ACTION</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb  5 11:11:32 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
There is probably enough oil in Iraq to repay the United States for the expense incurred in having to kick their stupid, suicidal, fanatical asses... not once but twice.<br><br>
What ever happened to the idea of &quot;spoils of war?&quot;<br><br>
Why negotiate with a man, Saddam Hussien, who never honors what he says in the first place?<br><br>
Who has the strength to tell Russia and France &quot;Shame on you for selling this Islamic idiot sensitive stuff to poison the world with...&quot;  and add, &quot;Oops! look like you made a bad investment!&quot;  and suggest &quot;Why don't you guys try selling Saddam food and medicine and things for deprived children?&quot;<br><br>
However, it has become a sad situation, a situation where action must replace words.<br><br>
If we're going to experience the expense and trauma of opening the chest cavity...let's not forget to do the corrective surgery!<br><br>
MTF
